description: The trail is steep from the very beginning, and only levels off at a meadow at around the half way point.  You are in the trees 3/4 of the way until you reach the tree line and make the last big push up to the summit.  Good 360 views of the surrounding area.
directions: Drive approx 80km East of Prince George, there are a good many signs telling you where the trail head is, parking is on the left side of the highway, and there is a large sign at the trail head.
title: Viking Ridge (snowshoe)
